+I need you to set up a git-based auto-deploy pipeline for this resume website project. Please do the following steps in order:
+
+1. Run "git status" to check if a git repo exists, if not run "git init"
+2. Create a .gitignore file ignoring .DS_Store, *.swp, .env, and editor files
+3. Create a deploy.sh script that runs: git add -A && git commit -m "deploy: $(date '+%Y-%m-%d %H:%M')" && git push origin main
+4. Make deploy.sh executable with chmod +x
+5. Create a README.md that says: "Chad's resume site for obsidiancloud.org — deployed automatically via Cloudflare Pages"
+6. Run git add -A and make the first commit with message "initial: resume site launch"
+
+Do not push yet — stop after the first commit. I will add the GitHub remote manually.

